atst.giss.abplc

Interface IPlcTag

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PlcTag

    public interface IPlcTag
    The public interface containing constants and methods used to operate with PlcTag objects.

    The constants defined include the types of PLC tags used by the GIS, these are:

    • CStatus — all GISS components and controllers use a CStatus PLC read tag to read the current hardware status from the GIS.
    • Cmds — all GISS controllers use a Cmds PLC write tag to write commands to the GIS to operate enclosure hardware.
    • Pos — all GISS tracking controllers use a Pos PLC write tag to write demand position to the GIS to move their tracking mechanism.
    • CPos — all GISS tracking controllers use a CPos PLC read tag to read the current tracking mechanism position from the GIS.

    The tag types which a component/controller uses are discovered by querying the propertyDB. All information required to operate with the tag (name, pcFormat, direction, etc.) are obtained from the component's entries in the propertyDB when a PlcTag object is created using PlcTag.PlcTag(String).

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Get the name of the PLC tag this object represents.

        The name of the tag is the identifier of the tag in the GIS PLC. The object's tag name is set on creation and is immutable.

        Returns:
        The tag's name.

      • getPcFormatString

        java.lang.String getPcFormatString()
        Get this tag's PLCIO pcFormat string.

        The tag's pcFormat string fully describes the data types and length of the data contained in the tag. The tag object's pcFormat string is set on creation and is immutable.

        Returns:
        The tag's pcFormat string.

      • getPcFormatTypeAL

        java.util.ArrayList<atst.giss.abplc.PlcioPcFormatType> getPcFormatTypeAL()
        Get the ArrayList containing all type descriptors contained in this tag's PLCIO pcFormat string.

        Each element in the list is a PlcioPcFormatType object and the list's order matches the order they are defined in the pcFormat string.

        Returns:
        An ArrayList containing this tag's type descriptors.

      • getDirection

        int getDirection()
        Get the communication direction of this tag - one of READ or WRITE.

        The direction of a tag object is set on creation and is immutable.

        Returns:
        The direction of this tag, either DIRECTION_READ or DIRECTION_WRITE.

        A String array containing the tag's values.

      • getMemberValue

        java.lang.String getMemberValue(java.lang.String itemName)
        Get the current value of the tag member containing the given tag's item.

        The value is not read from the PLC, the tag's member value containing the named tag item, currently stored in the object is the value returned.

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        the tag's member value in which the tag item is contained.

      • getCacheTagItemValues

        IAttributeTable getCacheTagItemValues()
        Get all of this tag's data items from the Cache and return in AttributeTable.

        The values are not read from the PLC; the data items belonging to this tag currently stored in the Cache are used to populate the returned table.

        Returns:
        Attribute table containing the tag data item values currently stored in Cache.

      • setCacheTagItemValues

        void setCacheTagItemValues(IAttributeTable newValues)
        Set the tag's data items in the Cache to values contained in AttributeTable.

        The values are not written to the PLC; the data items belonging to this stored in the Cache are updated to those in the table.

        Parameters:
        newValues - Attribute table containing the new tag data item values to be stored in the Cache.

      • setMemberValues

        int setMemberValues(java.lang.String[] newValues)
        Set the member values stored in this tag to new given values, also update the Cache to new values and update the last update time.

        No values are read from or written to the PLC, this tag's values are merely updated to store the new given values and the tag's data items in the Cache are updated to reflect the new values.

        Parameters:
        newValues - A String array containing the new values to be stored in the tagValues of this tag object and used to update the Cache.
        Returns:
        The length of this object's tagValues array or -1 if error occurred.

      • setMemberValues

        int setMemberValues()
        Set the member values stored in this tag to tag's data item values currently stored in the Cache and update the last update time.

        No values are read from or written to the PLC, this tag's values are merely updated from the tag's data items in the Cache. This method is used prior to passing the PlcTag object to the ABPlcioChannel#write(IPlcTag) to write this tag's values contained in Cache to the PLC.

        Returns:
        The length of this object's tagValues array or -1 if error occurred.

      • getValuesLastUpdateString

        java.lang.String getValuesLastUpdateString()
        Return a String representation of the time that this tag was last updated.

        If this tag is a READ tag then the time will be the time this tag was last read from the GIS. If this tag is a WRITE tag the time will be the time the tag was last written to the GIS.

        Returns:
        The time of the last update to this tag's values in format returned from atst.cs.util.AtstDate#getCurrent().toString().

      • tagValuesToString

        java.lang.String tagValuesToString()
        Return a String representation of this tag object's tag values.

        The format of the returned String is:
        {[0] = '&lt;member_0_value&gt;', [1] = '&lt;member_1_value&gt;', ..., [n] = '&lt;member_n_value&gt;'}

        Returns:
        A String representation of this tag's values.
